1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
<i>[Cinderella and Four Knights]</i>

2
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Subtitles by DramaFever

3
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
<i>[Cinderella and Four Knights]</i>

4
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:52,200
Ow, my head.

5
00:01:02,599 --> 00:01:05,800
Wow, that was one strange dream.

6
00:01:09,300 --> 00:01:10,800
Oof!

7
00:01:56,399 --> 00:02:00,499
Oh my gosh, I must be crazy!

8
00:02:07,399 --> 00:02:10,399
Wait, why am I happy?
Stop it! I'm not happy!

9
00:02:10,399 --> 00:02:11,899
I must be crazy!

10
00:02:11,899 --> 00:02:13,499
Oh man, I really must be crazy!

11
00:02:18,800 --> 00:02:21,499
Come on, Eun Ha Won!
Get it together, girl!

12
00:02:26,999 --> 00:02:28,499
What's going on?

13
00:02:35,600 --> 00:02:38,700
Hey, Eun Ha Won!
Are you okay?

14
00:02:38,700 --> 00:02:40,999
Ha Won!

15
00:03:05,200 --> 00:03:07,399
It seems like a minor concussion.

16
00:03:08,100 --> 00:03:09,800
Will she regain consciousness soon?

17
00:03:09,800 --> 00:03:12,399
Yes. She's merely asleep right now.

18
00:03:12,399 --> 00:03:15,300
Then, is it okay for us to transfer
the patient to a facility in Seoul?

19
00:03:15,300 --> 00:03:19,100
Yes. If there's a hospital that she
regularly goes to, you can do that.

20
00:03:19,100 --> 00:03:20,800
I'm sure she'll be getting up soon.

21
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:23,600
All right. I'll go and take care of
her discharge paperwork, then.

22
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:25,800
All right.

23
00:03:33,999 --> 00:03:37,399
Yeah. I'll take Ms. Ha Won to Seoul

24
00:03:37,399 --> 00:03:40,200
so I think it'd be best for you guys
to find your own way home.

25
00:03:40,700 --> 00:03:42,700
All right. Do that, then.

26
00:03:43,600 --> 00:03:45,499
You don't need to worry.

27
00:03:47,100 --> 00:03:51,300
He says that she's fine.
Yoon Sung said he'll take her to Seoul.

28
00:03:51,300 --> 00:03:53,600
What about us, then?
We don't need to go see her?

29
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:56,400
Right. He said that it was
only a minor concussion

30
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:58,199
and he wants us to go home and wait.

31
00:03:58,199 --> 00:04:02,400
Just how did she manage to fall over
in the bathroom, and get a concussion?

32
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:04,300
She really is...

33
00:04:08,100 --> 00:04:10,300
She really is a weird girl.

34
00:04:13,100 --> 00:04:16,499
Let's pack our things
and hurry back home.

35
00:04:16,499 --> 00:04:19,600
Yeah. It's not like we'd do anything by
ourselves without her around, anyway.

36
00:04:24,499 --> 00:04:26,300
Aren't you going to go
and pack your things?

37
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:28,999
What?

38
00:04:28,999 --> 00:04:30,499
It won't take me too long to pack.

39
00:04:30,499 --> 00:04:31,800
I'll pack my things too,
and come out, then.

40
00:04:31,800 --> 00:04:33,100
Wait for me.

41
00:05:00,499 --> 00:05:03,199
Um, excuse me.

42
00:05:03,199 --> 00:05:06,600
Oh, you're awake?

43
00:05:06,600 --> 00:05:11,100
What day is it today?

44
00:05:11,100 --> 00:05:14,100
It's the 15th.

45
00:05:14,100 --> 00:05:15,100
Huh?

46
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:18,400
What the...

47
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:20,499
not even a single day has gone by?

48
00:05:20,499 --> 00:05:21,499
Excuse me?

49
00:05:21,499 --> 00:05:25,199
I mean, usually when people
pass out and stuff

50
00:05:25,199 --> 00:05:27,900
and then wake up,
a week or so has gone by.

51
00:05:27,900 --> 00:05:29,400
Isn't that how it usually is?

52
00:05:30,100 --> 00:05:33,300
Thankfully, that's not the
case with you, so don't worry.

53
00:05:35,999 --> 00:05:38,199
Hey, are you okay?

54
00:05:38,199 --> 00:05:41,499
Oh, um... yeah, I think so.

55
00:05:41,499 --> 00:05:46,900
I was super worried about you because
you were passed out in the bathroom!

56
00:05:46,900 --> 00:05:49,800
- Aw, you were?
- Yeah!

57
00:05:49,800 --> 00:05:52,199
Oh yeah! Where's everyone else?

58
00:05:52,199 --> 00:05:55,800
Mr. Yoon Sung only brought you here.
He was in a huge rush.

59
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:59,100
Oh. But, um, Ja Young.

60
00:05:59,100 --> 00:06:03,999
When people usually pass out, don't
people get temporary amnesia

61
00:06:03,999 --> 00:06:08,100
or something like that, and not remember
anything that happened the night before?

62
00:06:08,100 --> 00:06:10,300
What's with you?

63
00:06:23,100 --> 00:06:25,300
Oh, never mind.
It's nothing.

64
00:06:25,300 --> 00:06:28,425
- Are you really okay?
- Yeah. I'm fine.

65
00:06:33,100 --> 00:06:35,999
I was quite worried about you.
I'm quite relieved.

66
00:06:35,999 --> 00:06:39,699
Oh. I'm sorry, Mister.
Because of me, you...

67
00:06:39,699 --> 00:06:43,400
Oh, let's hurry back!
I'm sure the rest of them are waiting.

68
00:06:43,400 --> 00:06:46,499
No. You must go to Seoul
and get a cast put on your leg.

69
00:06:46,499 --> 00:06:48,600
I've made an appointment for you at a
hospital that is owned by Haneul Group.

70
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:51,800
All they did here
was emergency first aid.

71
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:53,300
A cast?

72
00:06:55,499 --> 00:06:58,400
They said that you
sprained your ankle, too.

73
00:06:58,400 --> 00:07:02,800
Oh man, are you serious?

74
00:07:04,523 --> 00:07:06,800
Please get on.
I'll escort you to the car.

75
00:07:18,499 --> 00:07:20,600
Huh? She left all her clothes here.

76
00:07:35,199 --> 00:07:36,999
How tacky.

77
00:07:38,300 --> 00:07:41,300
Why does she always focus on
such unimportant things?

78
00:07:42,300 --> 00:07:44,199
What are you doing?

79
00:07:44,199 --> 00:07:45,300
Huh?

80
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:50,999
Oh, nothing.

81
00:07:52,900 --> 00:07:54,900
Let's go.

82
00:07:59,499 --> 00:08:01,600
What about everyone else?

83
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:04,199
They've taken another car,
and are on their way back to Seoul.

84
00:08:04,199 --> 00:08:08,000
Oh. Did I cut this trip short
for everyone?

85
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:09,099
It's quite all right, Ms. Ha Won.

86
00:08:09,099 --> 00:08:13,099
None of them would've come
if it hadn't been for you, anyway.

87
00:08:17,800 --> 00:08:19,599
What is it?

88
00:08:19,599 --> 00:08:22,199
You seemed to have quite
a low tolerance for alcohol!

89
00:08:22,199 --> 00:08:26,400
You didn't even seem like you had a lot,
but you passed out before we knew it!

90
00:08:26,400 --> 00:08:29,099
I saw a side of you that
I've never seen, Mister!

91
00:08:29,099 --> 00:08:33,319
Please... um... erase that memory
from your mind, ma'am.

92
00:08:33,319 --> 00:08:36,500
Oh, your face is all red, Mister!

93
00:08:36,500 --> 00:08:39,599
I... suppose that you didn't
get drunk, then, Ms. Ha Won?

94
00:08:39,599 --> 00:08:41,400
Well, I--

95
00:08:43,500 --> 00:08:46,800
No. I was super drunk last night, too.

96
00:08:46,800 --> 00:08:50,199
And because of that, I don't remember
a single thing that happened last night.

97
00:08:50,199 --> 00:08:52,400
Did something happen last night?

98
00:08:52,400 --> 00:08:56,000
Um, no.
Nothing happened.

99
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:57,800
But you just said that you
don't remember anything.

100
00:08:57,800 --> 00:08:59,500
Well, that is...

101
00:08:59,500 --> 00:09:04,400
Yes, um, I don't remember anything.
But nothing really happened.

102
00:09:19,199 --> 00:09:21,599
You've stretched the tendon
in your ankle.

103
00:09:21,599 --> 00:09:22,800
It's not a serious injury

104
00:09:22,800 --> 00:09:25,199
so you'll be fine if you're careful
with it for the next couple of days.

105
00:09:25,199 --> 00:09:27,099
Yes, thank you.

106
00:09:28,199 --> 00:09:30,400
Have you used crutches before?

107
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:34,599
It's hard to get used to them at first,
but they'll be quite useful when you do.

108
00:09:37,199 --> 00:09:39,599
- Can she go now?
- Yes.

109
00:09:39,599 --> 00:09:41,000
Please schedule your next appointment.

110
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:43,199
And be extra careful
for the next couple of days!

111
00:09:43,199 --> 00:09:45,300
Yes, I will.

112
00:09:50,400 --> 00:09:52,199
Mister!

113
00:09:55,500 --> 00:09:56,500
Let's go.

114
00:10:04,599 --> 00:10:06,000
<i>[Organ Transplantation Center]</i>

115
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:07,699
Organ Transplantation?

116
00:10:13,599 --> 00:10:16,800
It really won't be easy
to find an organ donor.

117
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:19,400
Oh... I see.

118
00:10:19,400 --> 00:10:22,300
It'd be best for him to tell their
family about their condition outright

119
00:10:22,300 --> 00:10:23,900
and find a donor among
his family members--

120
00:10:23,900 --> 00:10:27,300
He's staunchly against that idea.

121
00:10:27,300 --> 00:10:30,900
We have no other options
to offer you, at present.

122
00:10:30,900 --> 00:10:33,599
All I can tell you to do now is wait.

123
00:10:34,099 --> 00:10:39,500
All right. If you do find a donor,
please contact me.

124
00:10:39,500 --> 00:10:40,900
I will.

125
00:10:53,900 --> 00:10:57,099
- Um, Mister.
- Yes?

126
00:10:59,900 --> 00:11:02,300
Oh, it's nothing.
Let's hurry and go.

127
00:11:48,300 --> 00:11:50,400
We need to talk.

128
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:53,500
About what?

129
00:11:53,500 --> 00:11:55,099
About last night...

130
00:11:55,099 --> 00:11:56,699
Oh, that?

131
00:11:57,199 --> 00:11:59,099
Let's just pretend that it didn't happen.

132
00:12:00,199 --> 00:12:01,400
What?

133
00:12:01,400 --> 00:12:03,199
It's simple. Let's just pretend
that none of that happened.

134
00:12:03,199 --> 00:12:04,599
Okay?

135
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:40,199
What is it?

136
00:12:41,300 --> 00:12:43,400
Did something happen?

137
00:12:43,400 --> 00:12:46,599
Um, no.

138
00:12:57,599 --> 00:12:59,300
Eun Ha Won!

139
00:13:07,500 --> 00:13:11,000
Are you okay? You even
have to use crutches now?

140
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:13,099
Oh, it's only for a couple of days.

141
00:13:13,099 --> 00:13:15,199
Whoa!

142
00:13:26,099 --> 00:13:29,599
I'm fine!

143
00:13:31,800 --> 00:13:34,000
What a shame.
That must be so uncomfortable.

144
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:35,800
It doesn't hurt, or anything?

145
00:13:35,800 --> 00:13:39,500
They said that I just stretched
my tendon out a bit. I'm fine.

146
00:13:39,500 --> 00:13:42,000
You should've been careful.

147
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:44,500
I'll be your human crutch.

148
00:13:45,400 --> 00:13:48,300
Even though she's not your fiancee?

149
00:13:48,500 --> 00:13:51,699
- Ms. Celebrity! I'll help you.
- No!

150
00:13:52,900 --> 00:13:57,300
Um, it's because I'm not quite
used to them yet. I'll be fine soon.

151
00:13:57,800 --> 00:13:59,900
I'll help you, Ms. Ha Won.

152
00:14:00,800 --> 00:14:05,199
Then, can you hold these for me, Mister?

153
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:17,000
Why is she hopping off like that,
as if she's running away from us?

154
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:19,099
What's with her now?

155
00:14:24,500 --> 00:14:28,199
Let's go.
I'll take you home.

156
00:14:46,599 --> 00:14:50,599
Good work. Ms. Ha Won
is fine now, I presume?

157
00:14:50,599 --> 00:14:54,099
Yes. I've brought her back to Sky House.

158
00:14:54,099 --> 00:14:57,400
I was planning to get some rest here,
and keep it a secret from the kids.

159
00:14:57,400 --> 00:15:00,599
But instead, I almost got caught.

160
00:15:00,599 --> 00:15:03,099
How long are you planning
to hide your condition, Chairman?

161
00:15:03,099 --> 00:15:07,099
I don't know.
Until I die, perhaps?

162
00:15:07,099 --> 00:15:11,000
Honey! How could you say
something like that?

163
00:15:12,099 --> 00:15:15,500
Is it all right for him
to be discharged?

164
00:15:15,500 --> 00:15:18,000
His hepatic cirrhosis
is getting worse by the day.

165
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:22,099
It won't be long before
his liver fails completely.

166
00:15:22,099 --> 00:15:24,099
The only option left to us now is...

167
00:15:24,099 --> 00:15:26,800
It's fine. Whatever.

168
00:15:26,800 --> 00:15:30,400
- I'll quit drinking, and--
- You must receive a transplant.

169
00:15:30,400 --> 00:15:33,000
I thought you said you added my name on
the list of people looking for donors.

170
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:37,099
Yes. That is true, but a fitting
donor for you has yet to...

171
00:15:37,099 --> 00:15:39,800
Well, I'm sure we'll find one
soon enough.

172
00:15:40,699 --> 00:15:42,000
Isn't that right?

173
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:43,300
Chairman!

174
00:15:43,300 --> 00:15:47,599
What good will it do anyone to go
around telling everyone that I'm sick?

175
00:15:47,599 --> 00:15:49,699
Let's go.

176
00:15:49,699 --> 00:15:50,699
Yes.

177
00:15:55,500 --> 00:15:57,900
I'll take that, ma'am.

178
00:15:57,900 --> 00:15:59,800
Thank you.

179
00:15:59,800 --> 00:16:02,699
No. This is merely a part of my duty.

180
00:16:03,800 --> 00:16:08,800
It would've been quite nice
if I had a son like you.

181
00:16:08,800 --> 00:16:10,599
You're too kind.

182
00:16:25,500 --> 00:16:28,500
Did something happen
between you and Ha Won yesterday?

183
00:16:28,500 --> 00:16:31,000
Huh?
Um, why?

184
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:34,400
You two seemed a bit off,
back at Sky House.

185
00:16:34,400 --> 00:16:36,000
No, I don't know about that.

186
00:16:36,500 --> 00:16:39,599
It kind of seemed as if
Ha Won was avoiding you.

187
00:16:40,399 --> 00:16:45,399
She probably feels embarrassed about
the fact that she tripped and fell over.

188
00:16:45,399 --> 00:16:50,300
Figures. We all drank way too much.
My head still hurts a bit.

189
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:53,899
Yeah.

190
00:16:54,399 --> 00:16:57,200
Wow, I feel like I have a really
bad headache coming on.

191
00:16:57,200 --> 00:17:01,099
You were quite cute when
you were drunk, Kang Ji Woon.

192
00:17:02,800 --> 00:17:04,899
Stop messing around, punk!

193
00:17:04,899 --> 00:17:09,099
No, really. It's been a while
since I saw you smiling like that.

194
00:17:10,200 --> 00:17:12,200
Really?

195
00:17:12,200 --> 00:17:15,099
Are you the daughter of the people
who live here, by any chance?

196
00:17:15,800 --> 00:17:17,399
Yes.

197
00:17:17,399 --> 00:17:19,599
Is your father home?

198
00:17:19,599 --> 00:17:21,399
No, he went on a business trip.

199
00:17:21,399 --> 00:17:22,800
Oh.

200
00:17:25,599 --> 00:17:27,099
Who are you?

201
00:17:27,099 --> 00:17:30,399
Oh, it's nothing.
We'll come back another time.

202
00:17:38,200 --> 00:17:40,700
What's with those guys?

203
00:17:41,200 --> 00:17:44,599
I don't know. Maybe they're
people that my dad knows?

204
00:17:45,099 --> 00:17:46,399
Will you be all right?

205
00:17:46,399 --> 00:17:50,399
Yeah. I want to head in,
wash up, and get some rest.

206
00:17:51,599 --> 00:17:53,899
All right.

207
00:17:53,899 --> 00:17:56,500
Thanks for dropping me off.

208
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:17,500
Yes, go ahead.

209
00:18:20,200 --> 00:18:23,200
Really?

210
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:25,399
I'll head over there right now.

211
00:18:50,500 --> 00:18:53,099
<i>Did something happen
between you and Ha Won?</i>

212
00:18:53,099 --> 00:18:55,800
<i>It seemed like she was avoiding you.</i>

213
00:19:26,099 --> 00:19:28,500
I knew this would happen.

214
00:19:30,800 --> 00:19:33,099
Don't you want my help?

215
00:19:34,099 --> 00:19:36,200
I was about to change
into something else.

216
00:19:37,200 --> 00:19:38,800
Yeah.

217
00:19:39,399 --> 00:19:41,000
Get out!

218
00:19:41,800 --> 00:19:43,099
Nah.

219
00:19:43,099 --> 00:19:44,500
Hey!

220
00:19:50,800 --> 00:19:55,000
Wow! Is this really all for Eun Ha Won?

221
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:59,800
Yeah. She's injured,
so she needs to eat up.

222
00:19:59,800 --> 00:20:01,500
Isn't that right?

223
00:20:01,500 --> 00:20:05,200
Oh, of course!
I'll bring this to her.

224
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:07,399
- Please be careful.
- All right.

225
00:20:11,800 --> 00:20:15,899
How could this be?
No way. This can't be.

226
00:20:15,899 --> 00:20:20,500
Hey, what about my clothes?
Why don't you have anything with you?

227
00:20:20,500 --> 00:20:22,800
Your wardrobe is a crime against fashion.

228
00:20:22,800 --> 00:20:24,899
There's nothing in there
that's actually worth wearing!

229
00:20:24,899 --> 00:20:28,099
That's not true. I'm sure that there are
tons of things worth wearing in there.

230
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:31,500
- Just wait.
- Where are you going?

231
00:20:31,500 --> 00:20:32,899
To buy some clothes that
are actually half-decent!

232
00:20:35,599 --> 00:20:36,800
- Oh my--
- Hey!

233
00:20:36,800 --> 00:20:38,399
- You surprised me!
- You surprised me!

234
00:20:38,399 --> 00:20:40,399
You almost knocked everything over!

235
00:20:40,399 --> 00:20:43,000
- And why are you here?
- Oh, for Eun Ha Won.

236
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:45,200
Food is the most important
thing to her, as you know.

237
00:20:45,200 --> 00:20:46,200
And what about you?

238
00:20:46,200 --> 00:20:49,300
Oh, I just had a couple of things
I had to take care of.

239
00:20:49,300 --> 00:20:51,000
Get out of my way, already!

240
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:53,099
Hey, be careful!

241
00:20:53,099 --> 00:20:54,599
Why, you little!

242
00:20:54,599 --> 00:20:56,200
Damn it.

243
00:21:00,399 --> 00:21:05,700
All right. Ta-da!
Your breakfast!

244
00:21:05,700 --> 00:21:10,099
Wow, Kang Seo Woo!
I'm totally touched!

245
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:18,099
I'm not the one who made all this.

246
00:21:18,099 --> 00:21:21,000
I know. It was probably
Ms. Beolgyo who made this.

247
00:21:21,000 --> 00:21:23,000
She's quite a generous person!

248
00:21:23,500 --> 00:21:25,399
No, it's not that she's
a generous person.

249
00:21:25,399 --> 00:21:27,700
It's just that you have
a crazy-huge appetite.

250
00:21:36,899 --> 00:21:40,000
- That's weird.
- What?

251
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:42,099
Why are you eating so little?

252
00:21:42,099 --> 00:21:44,599
I don't really have much of an appetite.

253
00:21:44,599 --> 00:21:45,599
