You know that, don't you?

376
00:30:42,800 --> 00:30:45,200
You know that they go crazy
when something juicy pops up!

377
00:30:46,300 --> 00:30:49,899
Really? Then give them something
even crazier to report on.

378
00:30:49,899 --> 00:30:52,399
And where in the world would we get that?

379
00:30:53,500 --> 00:30:55,599
You don't mean "that," do you?

380
00:30:55,599 --> 00:30:58,800
Yeah. I have something that's
even juicier than those photos.

381
00:31:01,500 --> 00:31:05,300
Don't let your imagination run wild.
It's nothing like that, okay?

382
00:31:10,200 --> 00:31:14,000
My heart totally
skipped a beat just now.

383
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:18,200
When did my Seo Woo grow up so much?

384
00:31:18,200 --> 00:31:21,700
Come on, snap back to reality!

385
00:31:25,800 --> 00:31:29,500
What the heck? He can't even
remember what happened?

386
00:31:29,500 --> 00:31:32,599
Did he really only do that
because he was under the influence?

387
00:31:32,599 --> 00:31:37,200
That's not fair!

388
00:31:37,200 --> 00:31:39,800
Or, maybe I'm wrong.

389
00:31:39,800 --> 00:31:42,599
Is it actually better that
he forgot about everything?

390
00:31:42,599 --> 00:31:44,700
But still, this isn't right!

391
00:31:44,700 --> 00:31:48,099
Damn him.
Should I go yell at him?

392
00:31:49,599 --> 00:31:53,200
Oh, but even if I do, he won't
be able to remember anything!

393
00:31:53,200 --> 00:31:55,599
Oh, forget it!

394
00:31:58,800 --> 00:32:00,099
