and cut the line, just to save my skin.

423
00:33:30,200 --> 00:33:33,300
- But this might be the last option--
- I know how you must feel.

424
00:33:33,300 --> 00:33:39,099
But there are some lines
that you just can't cut, in life.

425
00:33:39,099 --> 00:33:44,200
There are things that no
amount of money can buy

426
00:33:44,200 --> 00:33:46,399
and there are things that
one must never buy, too.

427
00:33:48,499 --> 00:33:51,800
What, do you pity me that much?

428
00:33:53,800 --> 00:33:55,499
No, sir.

429
00:33:55,499 --> 00:34:00,399
I was just thinking to myself
about what a great man I serve.

430
00:34:02,399 --> 00:34:05,300
You've worked quite hard.

431
00:34:05,300 --> 00:34:07,300
You must be, to notice something
as insignificant as that.

432
00:34:30,300 --> 00:34:32,600
<i>About what happened last night...</i>

433
00:34:32,600 --> 00:34:36,300
Oh, that? Let's just pretend
that it never happened.

434
00:34:36,300 --> 00:34:37,300
What?

435
00:34:37,300 --> 00:34:39,499
It's simple. Let's just pretend
that none of that happened.

436
00:34:39,499 --> 00:34:40,800
Okay?

437
00:34:49,200 --> 00:34:51,300
