00:41:12,200 --> 00:41:15,200
Why did I take this, though?

498
00:41:15,200 --> 00:41:17,300
It's not like I want evidence
of what happened, or anything.

499
00:41:38,600 --> 00:41:40,399
<i>Are you sleeping?</i>

500
00:41:40,399 --> 00:41:42,499
<i>Come out to the balcony for a second.</i>

501
00:41:42,800 --> 00:41:44,499
<i>[To: Eun Ha Won]</i>

502
00:41:48,800 --> 00:41:52,700
- Ta-da!
- Wow! What is all this?

503
00:41:52,700 --> 00:41:55,399
- A midnight snack?
- Hurry and sit.

504
00:41:57,399 --> 00:42:00,399
Wow, I really wanted to
eat this kind of stuff!

505
00:42:00,399 --> 00:42:02,499
You're the best!

506
00:42:02,499 --> 00:42:06,899
Wow, seasoned fried chicken?
It looks so delicious!

507
00:42:06,899 --> 00:42:09,800
Hey, how did you know that
this stuff is the good stuff?

508
00:42:09,800 --> 00:42:12,499
Wow, this looks delicious!

509
00:42:17,800 --> 00:42:19,899
You're totally touched, right?

510
00:42:19,899 --> 00:42:22,499
See, this is why chicks
are crazy for me.

511
00:42:22,499 --> 00:42:24,399
What, did another girl confess
her feelings to you lately?

512
00:42:24,399 --> 00:42:26,499
As if you need to reaffirm that fact!

513
00:42:26,999 --> 00:42:29,499
You're not that popular lately, though.

514
00:42:29,999 --> 00:42:31,899
Hey, what are you talking about?

515
00:42:31,899 --> 00:42:34,800
Does anyone really like you
for who you are?

516
00:42:36,600 --> 00:42:38,600
Like Hye Ji does?

517
00:42:41,200 --> 00:42:42,800
Well, duh.

518
00:42:44,399 --> 00:42:47,999
Hey! You're being really mean, you know.

519
00:42:47,999 --> 00:42:52,600
- What now?
- You know Hye Ji really likes you.

520
00:42:54,899 --> 00:42:59,999
I think that Hye Ji
is really quite brave.

521
00:42:59,999 --> 00:43:04,300
She's honest about her feelings,
and tries her best to be loved.

522
00:43:05,200 --> 00:43:07,999
Do you know how hard that is to do?

523
00:43:08,800 --> 00:43:10,999
She's like a tree.

524
00:43:10,999 --> 00:43:12,800
She's planted her roots to one spot

525
00:43:12,800 --> 00:43:15,200
and won't be shaken,
no matter what comes her way.

526
00:43:16,800 --> 00:43:18,899
What about me, then?

527
00:43:19,499 --> 00:43:21,600
You're...

528
00:43:22,100 --> 00:43:26,499
like the wind, that just keeps blowing,
completely unaware of her efforts.

529
00:43:26,499 --> 00:43:29,800
In other words, you're a real player!

530
00:43:30,600 --> 00:43:32,399
Geez.

531
00:43:34,600 --> 00:43:37,100
I wonder if I could ever bring
myself to do what she's doing.

532
00:43:39,399 --> 00:43:41,700
Do you think you could,
if you were in her shoes?

533
00:43:43,600 --> 00:43:47,800
I never had a chance to date because
I was too busy with part-time jobs

534
00:43:47,800 --> 00:43:50,999
so I really know nothing
about how that must feel

535
00:43:50,999 --> 00:43:54,100
but even I could tell whether or
not her feelings for you are real.

536
00:43:56,200 --> 00:44:01,999
Hye Ji really has
earnest feelings for you.

537
00:44:03,399 --> 00:44:07,499
Stop eating.
It doesn't suit you.

538
00:44:07,499 --> 00:44:12,499
But I feel like you're that
way sometimes, too.

539
00:44:12,499 --> 00:44:13,899
What do you mean?

540
00:44:15,100 --> 00:44:18,200
I'm talking about the way
you look at Hye Ji!

541
00:44:18,200 --> 00:44:20,499
You're so rude to her
when you talk to her

542
00:44:20,499 --> 00:44:25,200
but sometimes,
you look at her quite tenderly.

543
00:44:27,100 --> 00:44:29,999
I'm not that complicated, you know.

544
00:44:31,800 --> 00:44:35,100
But keep this in mind.

545
00:44:35,100 --> 00:44:38,999
There's no tree that will wait
around for you forever.

546
00:44:38,999 --> 00:44:40,999
Don't regret this later.

547
00:44:43,999 --> 00:44:46,200
Eat up.

548
00:44:48,800 --> 00:44:50,399
Hey!

549
00:46:28,600 --> 00:46:31,300
I'm visiting someone who's sick, so
please don't make it too over-the-top.

550
00:46:31,300 --> 00:46:33,100
Yes, I understand.

551
00:46:55,499 --> 00:46:57,300
Here.

552
00:46:58,100 --> 00:46:59,600
Happy?

553
00:46:59,800 --> 00:47:02,111
<i>[Kang Seo Woo Flees While Wearing
Jungsan Girls' High Uniform!]</i>

554
00:47:05,800 --> 00:47:08,999
I must be a genius, Manager.

555
00:47:08,999 --> 00:47:11,100
Whatever. Let's not talk
about this anymore.

556
00:47:11,100 --> 00:47:13,399
Come on, check out these comments!

557
00:47:13,899 --> 00:47:16,499
"Kang Seo Woo looks cool,
no matter what he does!"

558
00:47:16,499 --> 00:47:18,200
"He's so adorable!"

559
00:47:18,200 --> 00:47:20,300
"Shield your eyes, my body!"

560
00:47:20,899 --> 00:47:22,399
See? Everyone's going crazy over these.

561
00:47:22,399 --> 00:47:23,899
Wait, really?

562
00:47:25,999 --> 00:47:29,300
See? I told you!
I'm successful no matter what I do.

563
00:47:29,300 --> 00:47:32,800
My Seo Woo... you're all
grown up now, aren't you?

564
00:47:32,800 --> 00:47:34,200
You're all grown up!

565
00:47:35,899 --> 00:47:38,600
Maybe I should've just said
that we're dating.

566
00:47:50,100 --> 00:47:52,100
You're outside?

567
00:47:52,100 --> 00:47:54,600
Huh? What brings you here?

568
00:47:54,600 --> 00:47:57,300
I came by because I was
wondering how you were doing.

569
00:47:57,300 --> 00:47:59,499
Oh... thanks!

570
00:47:59,499 --> 00:48:02,700
I'm not that badly hurt, though.

571
00:48:02,700 --> 00:48:05,499
I felt like you'd pretty much
have access to anything here

572
00:48:05,499 --> 00:48:08,100
so I brought you a bouquet of flowers.

573
00:48:08,100 --> 00:48:11,100
Wow! Thanks!

574
00:48:11,600 --> 00:48:13,499
Wow, they're so pretty!

575
00:48:13,499 --> 00:48:15,700
Oh, do you want to come in for a second?

576
00:48:16,300 --> 00:48:17,999
Sure.

577
00:48:25,399 --> 00:48:27,100
Thanks.

578
00:48:27,700 --> 00:48:28,899
It's this way.

579
00:48:38,499 --> 00:48:41,100
So this is your room?

580
00:48:41,100 --> 00:48:44,499
Oh, it's not my room, per se.

581
00:48:44,499 --> 00:48:48,499
It's really nice. Looks like the
Chairman put a lot of work into it!

582
00:48:48,499 --> 00:48:51,100
Well, you know.

583
00:48:55,800 --> 00:48:58,999
Thank you, Ms. Beolgyo!
I should've gotten this myself!

584
00:48:58,999 --> 00:49:02,200
What are you saying, with that leg?

585
00:49:02,200 --> 00:49:03,899
Don't such say such things.

586
00:49:03,899 --> 00:49:08,200
I'll come and clean this up
after you're finished.

587
00:49:08,200 --> 00:49:10,499
Yes, ma'am. Thank you.

588
00:49:18,399 --> 00:49:22,100
- Then, have a pleasant time conversing.
- We will!

589
00:49:23,499 --> 00:49:24,999
Eat up, Hye Ji!

590
00:49:24,999 --> 00:49:25,999
Oh, okay.

591
00:49:27,499 --> 00:49:30,600
Looks like everyone here likes you.

592
00:49:31,300 --> 00:49:32,800
Me?

593
00:49:33,300 --> 00:49:35,399
Well, you know.

594
00:49:35,899 --> 00:49:37,800
Sometimes, I'm a bit jealous of you.

595
00:49:37,800 --> 00:49:40,999
You get along so well
with all of the Kang Cousins.

596
00:49:40,999 --> 00:49:43,399
Oh, it only seems like that
on the surface!

597
00:49:43,399 --> 00:49:45,100
Everyone here actually fights a lot!

598
00:49:49,200 --> 00:49:50,399
Sorry.

599
00:49:50,399 --> 00:49:54,100
My head itches because I couldn't
wash my hair for a couple of days.

600
00:49:54,100 --> 00:49:55,800
Want me to help you?

601
00:49:55,800 --> 00:50:00,399
Oh, it's okay! I hurt my ankle
and not my wrist, after all.

602
00:50:02,200 --> 00:50:04,999
Okay, then. Go ahead.

603
00:50:04,999 --> 00:50:07,100
Sorry. I'll be back soon.

604
00:50:53,499 --> 00:50:54,999
Are you sleeping?

605
00:51:32,800 --> 00:51:34,999
What are you doing?

606
00:51:42,700 --> 00:51:44,399
Get out.

607
00:51:47,800 --> 00:51:49,100
We need to talk.

608
00:51:49,100 --> 00:51:50,700
I have nothing to say to you.

609
00:51:51,800 --> 00:51:55,600
I can't pretend that nothing
happened between us.

610
00:51:57,399 --> 00:51:58,999
Don't be like this.

611
00:51:58,999 --> 00:52:00,899
What am I to you?

612
00:52:02,300 --> 00:52:04,100
A friend?

613
00:52:04,100 --> 00:52:09,399
Or... the younger sister of my brother,
your friend that died?

614
00:52:13,399 --> 00:52:15,100
We don't have any kind of relationship.

615
00:52:19,800 --> 00:52:23,999
And does this also mean nothing to you?

616
00:52:23,999 --> 00:52:26,499
If you keep acting this way...

617
00:52:27,499 --> 00:52:29,700
I really won't ever see you again.

618
00:52:38,955 --> 00:52:40,399
You're not leaving?

619
00:52:41,999 --> 00:52:46,499
I'll... leave, then.

620
00:53:41,300 --> 00:53:44,700
Who's there?
Can you help me?

621
00:53:45,300 --> 00:53:46,399
Oh man!

622
00:53:59,300 --> 00:54:03,100
Hey. What are you doing down there?

623
00:54:03,100 --> 00:54:05,300
What happened?

624
00:54:05,800 --> 00:54:07,499
Well, uh...

625
00:54:07,499 --> 00:54:09,700
I was trying to wash my hair, and...

626
00:54:11,499 --> 00:54:15,499
Sorry, but can you call
Ms. Beolgyo for me?

627
00:54:15,999 --> 00:54:18,499
She... went out before.

628
00:54:18,499 --> 00:54:20,200
Oh... really?

629
00:54:21,399 --> 00:54:26,999
Then... I'm really sorry, but...

630
00:54:26,999 --> 00:54:28,700
But can you help me up?

631
00:54:29,600 --> 00:54:31,800
Sorry.

632
00:54:31,800 --> 00:54:33,999
Geez.

633
00:54:33,999 --> 00:54:35,600
Wait just a sec.

634
00:54:40,300 --> 00:54:43,899
Geez, way to go.
Stay still.

635
00:54:43,899 --> 00:54:44,899
Okay.

636
00:54:51,499 --> 00:54:52,899
Thanks!

637
00:54:57,100 --> 00:54:58,999
Um, thanks.

638
00:55:02,300 --> 00:55:07,100
- Hey. You...
- What?

639
00:55:07,100 --> 00:55:09,300
Are you planning to leave the bathroom
with your hair looking like that?

640
00:55:10,200 --> 00:55:11,999
Oh.

641
00:55:20,499 --> 00:55:23,999
Wow... no other guy but me
would do this for you!

642
00:55:24,999 --> 00:55:26,899
Thanks.

643
00:55:27,800 --> 00:55:31,100
Hey! You're getting water in my eyes!

644
00:55:31,100 --> 00:55:32,100
Ugh!

645
00:55:32,600 --> 00:55:34,300
All right, already!

646
00:55:35,300 --> 00:55:40,499
Ah, my ear! Oh no!
There's water in my ear!

647
00:55:40,499 --> 00:55:43,399
Geez, stop protesting so much!

648
00:55:45,399 --> 00:55:48,200
Hey, what are you doing?

649
00:55:48,200 --> 00:55:49,700
You have to dry it like this for it
to dry well. Just stay still, okay?

650
00:55:49,700 --> 00:55:51,800
I knew you'd do this!
No! I'll do it! It's fine!

651
00:55:51,800 --> 00:55:54,600
Oh, no, ma'am! You've hurt
your leg! Please, sit still.

652
00:55:54,600 --> 00:55:56,700
I told you, it's fine!
I'll do it! I'll...

653
00:56:10,200 --> 00:56:13,499
I told you, I'll do it myself!
Sheesh.

654
00:56:13,999 --> 00:56:17,100
Geez, you even complain
when I try to help you.

655
00:56:19,200 --> 00:56:22,600
The dryer's in the bathroom.

656
00:56:25,800 --> 00:56:27,999
Oh... thanks!

657
00:56:53,899 --> 00:56:55,300
Wait a sec.

658
00:57:07,499 --> 00:57:10,399
<i>If you keep acting like this...</i>

659
00:57:11,300 --> 00:57:13,700
<i>I won't see you ever again.</i>

660
00:57:42,499 --> 00:57:43,999
Hye Ji!

661
00:57:53,499 --> 00:57:55,600
What's wrong, Hye Ji?

662
00:58:54,999 --> 00:58:57,399
I told you not to make
Hye Ji cry, didn't I?

663
00:59:00,600 --> 00:59:04,999
Who do you think you are?
What gives you that right?

664
00:59:13,300 --> 00:59:16,100
Ji Woon has the right to say that.

665
00:59:34,899 --> 00:59:36,899
I...

666
00:59:38,100 --> 00:59:41,600
don't want to cry
because of Hyun Min anymore.

667
00:59:45,999 --> 00:59:48,800
I...

668
00:59:48,800 --> 00:59:50,899
want to take a break from you.

669
00:59:55,899 --> 00:59:57,999
Will you...

670
00:59:59,399 --> 01:00:01,700
accept me?

671
01:00:31,694 --> 01:00:34,694
Subtitles by DramaFever